26#include <sys/cdefs.h>
27__KERNEL_RCSID(0, "$NetBSD: nouveau_nvkm_subdev_bios_P0260.c,v 1.2 2018/08/27 04:58:33 riastradh Exp $");
28
29#include <subdev/bios.h>
30#include <subdev/bios/bit.h>
31#include <subdev/bios/P0260.h>
32
33u32
34nvbios_P0260Te(struct nvkm_bios *bios,
35 u8 *ver, u8 *hdr, u8 *cnt, u8 *len, u8 *xnr, u8 *xsz)
36{
37 struct bit_entry bit_P;
38 u32 data = 0x00000000;
39
40 if (!bit_entry(bios, 'P', &bit_P)) {
41 if (bit_P.version == 2 && bit_P.length > 0x63)
42 data = nvbios_rd32(bios, bit_P.offset + 0x60);
43 if (data) {
44 *ver = nvbios_rd08(bios, data + 0);
45 switch (*ver) {
46 case 0x10:
47 *hdr = nvbios_rd08(bios, data + 1);
48 *cnt = nvbios_rd08(bios, data + 2);
49 *len = 4;
50 *xnr = nvbios_rd08(bios, data + 3);
51 *xsz = 4;
52 return data;
53 default:
54 break;
55 }
56 }
57 }
58
59 return 0x00000000;
60}
61
62u32
63nvbios_P0260Ee(struct nvkm_bios *bios, int idx, u8 *ver, u8 *len)
64{
65 u8 hdr, cnt, xnr, xsz;
66 u32 data = nvbios_P0260Te(bios, ver, &hdr, &cnt, len, &xnr, &xsz);
67 if (data && idx < cnt)
68 return data + hdr + (idx * *len);
69 return 0x00000000;
70}
71
72u32
73nvbios_P0260Ep(struct nvkm_bios *bios, int idx, u8 *ver, u8 *len,
74 struct nvbios_P0260E *info)
75{
76 u32 data = nvbios_P0260Ee(bios, idx, ver, len);
77 memset(info, 0x00, sizeof(*info));
78 switch (!!data * *ver) {
79 case 0x10:
80 info->data = nvbios_rd32(bios, data);
81 return data;
82 default:
83 break;
84 }
85 return 0x00000000;
86}
87
88u32
89nvbios_P0260Xe(struct nvkm_bios *bios, int idx, u8 *ver, u8 *xsz)
90{
91 u8 hdr, cnt, len, xnr;
92 u32 data = nvbios_P0260Te(bios, ver, &hdr, &cnt, &len, &xnr, xsz);
93 if (data && idx < xnr)
94 return data + hdr + (cnt * len) + (idx * *xsz);
95 return 0x00000000;
96}
97
98u32
99nvbios_P0260Xp(struct nvkm_bios *bios, int idx, u8 *ver, u8 *hdr,
100 struct nvbios_P0260X *info)
101{
102 u32 data = nvbios_P0260Xe(bios, idx, ver, hdr);
103 memset(info, 0x00, sizeof(*info));
104 switch (!!data * *ver) {
105 case 0x10:
106 info->data = nvbios_rd32(bios, data);
107 return data;
108 default:
109 break;
110 }
111 return 0x00000000;
112}
